{"title": "Bible (Fenton) NT 04, 23, 01, 02: Holy Bible in Modern English, The: John, 1 John, Matthew, Mark", "description": "The ordering novelty in the New Testament is that it places the Gospel of John and the First Epistle of John at the beginning before the Gospel of Matthew, thus placing the Acts of the Apostles immediately after the Gospel of Luke.<br><br>Work on the translation began in 1853 by a London businessman called Ferrar Fenton (1832\u20131920). The complete Bible was first published in 1903, though parts were published as separate volumes during the preceding 11 years. The translation is noted for a rearranging of the books of the Bible into what the author believed was the correct chronological order. His translation of the New Testament is based on the Greek text of Westcott and Hort. (Introduction from Wikipedia)", "duration": 22546, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "9939", "name": " Ferrar Fenton Bible"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt21/John_FFB_1209.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["Bibles"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mark Penfold"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mark Penfold"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Diana Majlinger"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "David Lawrence"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - John 1-5", "readers": [2149], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bible_fenton_04_23_01_02_mp_1101_librivox/01_john_01_fenton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1785}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - John 6-9", "readers": [2149], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bible_fenton_04_23_01_02_mp_1101_librivox/02_john_02_fenton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1752}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - John 10-13", "readers": [2149], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bible_fenton_04_23_01_02_mp_1101_librivox/03_john_03_fenton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1530}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - John 14-17", "readers": [2149], "path": "https://www.archive.org/downloa